NUMBER 222
NAME Tribunal Chamber
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
This cold chamber is where those accused of crimes carrying penalties of death or banishment come to trial. There is a black chair placed in the center of the room where the accused sits. All others, whether they are the tribunes, spectators or witnesses, stand during Fayd trials. A marble codex stands next to the iron door leading outwards.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 943 ADJ1=97 VAL1=150 VAL2=221 VAL3=504 UNLOCKED
ITEM 1 251 ADJ1=187
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
The codex displays the laws and punishments of Fayd's justice system for all to read.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB READ 1

CLEARVERB

ECHO PLAYER By The Power Vested In Him By Shemri, Amilor, Rorin And
ECHO PLAYER Kaliban Upon His Day Of Coronation, The King Is The Law.
ECHO PLAYER Whatsoever He Surveys Is His Realm. Herein Are The His
ECHO PLAYER Laws Of Fayd, Governing Citizens Within The City Walls,
ECHO PLAYER Including The Graveyard And Catacombs And Having No
ECHO PLAYER Jurisdiction Without, Unless The King Does Specifically
ECHO PLAYER Instruct:%c
ECHO PLAYER The Crimes Punishable In Fayd By Warrant Number:%c
ECHO PLAYER   I:   Petty Theft: Filching Non-artifact Items Worth Less
ECHO PLAYER        Than 100 Gold. This includes items left on the ground
ECHO PLAYER         when crimianls are arrested.%c
ECHO PLAYER  II:   Grand Theft: Filching Non-artifact Items Worth 100
ECHO PLAYER        gold or more but less than 1,000 gold. This includes
ECHO PLAYER        items left on the ground when criminals are arrested.%c
ECHO PLAYER III:   Minor Dark Necromancy: The Casting Of Body Destruction
ECHO PLAYER        Spells and Wail of the Banshee.%c
ECHO PLAYER  IV:   Fraud: Claiming To Be A Known Citizen Of Fayd Whom
ECHO PLAYER        You Are Not Or Claiming To Hold Government, Official,
ECHO PLAYER        Clerical And/Or Royal Titles And Positions That You
ECHO PLAYER        Do Not, Otherwise, disguise is not a crime.%c
ECHO PLAYER   V:   Breaking And Entering: Using Force, Vandalism Or
ECHO PLAYER        Stealth To Enter Into An Area Not Belonging To You,
ECHO PLAYER        Or Where You Are Unwanted Or Prohibited.%c
ECHO PLAYER  VI:   Assault: An Action Taken Against Someone That
ECHO PLAYER        Threatens Their Life, Liberty Or Property, Or
ECHO PLAYER        Otherwise Makes Them Subject To Unwanted Dweomers,
ECHO PLAYER        Or Persistant Sexual Harrassment And/Or Unwelcomed
ECHO PLAYER        Physical Advances. (Once A Complaint Of Sexual
ECHO PLAYER        Harrassment Has Been Filed With A Lawkeeper
ECHO PLAYER        Continuing Such Behaviors Will Result In Assault
ECHO PLAYER        Charges.)%c
ECHO PLAYER        Heresy: Speaking The Name Of The Devourer Of Souls In
ECHO PLAYER        Public, Or Taking The Name Of Shemri, Amilor, Rorin
ECHO PLAYER        And/Or Kaliban In Vain, Or Defiling The Temples Of
ECHO PLAYER        Such Or Other Forms Of Sacralidge And Blasphemy.%c
ECHO PLAYER        Kidnapping: Dragging, Carrying, Dominating or
ECHO PLAYER        otherwise forceable taking a citizen from the City or
ECHO PLAYER        Anywhere with the intent to do them harm%c
ECHO PLAYER VII:   Major DARK Necromancy: Summoning, Consorting With Or
ECHO PLAYER        Creating Undead (This Includes Controlling Of Undead
ECHO PLAYER        Except For The Purposes Of Banishing Them), Or
ECHO PLAYER        Summoning Entities Whose Presence In The Realms Is
ECHO PLAYER        A Threat To Public Safety, Or Bringing Dangerous
ECHO PLAYER        Dominated Entities Into the City.%c
ECHO PLAYER        Aiding Or Abetting: Hiding The Whereabouts Of,
ECHO PLAYER        Healing,  Or Casting Helpful Spells On Warranted
ECHO PLAYER        Individuals, Or Guarding Them In Order To
ECHO PLAYER        Block Their Arrest.%c
ECHO PLAYER        Grand Theft II: Filching A Unique Artifact Or Item
ECHO PLAYER        Worth More Than 1,000 Gold. This includes items left
ECHO PLAYER        on the ground when criminals are arrested.%c
ECHO PLAYER VIII:  Murder: The Slaying Of A Citizen Or Visitor In Fayd.
ECHO PLAYER        Self Preservation is a defense to the crime of murder
ECHO PLAYER        if the response is a reasonable one The Highest Ranking
ECHO PLAYER        Member Of A Temple Or Guild  Present Has The Right To
ECHO PLAYER        Defend Or Seek Aid In The Defense Of The Temple Or Guild
ECHO PLAYER        Property Against Intruders Once Warning Is Given.
ECHO PLAYER        Death As The Result Of A Consentual Duel Shall Not Be
ECHO PLAYER        Considered Murder.%c
ECHO PLAYER IX:    Treason: Acting Against Or Obstructing The Agents Of
ECHO PLAYER        Law, Order, Government And/Or The Crown In Fayd.
ECHO PLAYER        Assaulting A Lawkeeper Or Royal Guard.%c
ECHO PLAYER There Must Be At Least Two Witnesses Other Than The Victim
ECHO PLAYER To Warrant Someone For Crime III Or Above (They Need Not Be
ECHO PLAYER Named Citizens. People Who Bear Witness From Behind Windows
ECHO PLAYER Or Who Are Among The Crowds On The Street Are Adequate Witnesses).%c
ECHO PLAYER In Cases Of Multiple or Repeated Murders, and Treason, Or
ECHO PLAYER Incidents Where Banishment or Obliteration Are In Order, Trials
ECHO PLAYER May Be Held At The Whim Of The King, Wherein He Shall Appoint A
ECHO PLAYER Jury Of Five. If the King Is Not Available, Or Unwilling, The
ECHO PLAYER Highest Ranking Lawkeeper Should Escort The Acused Outside of
ECHO PLAYER the City Gates for Banishment.%c
ECHO PLAYER Banished Individuals Who Illegally Enter The City and Are Caught
ECHO PLAYER Committing More Crimes Will Be Subject To Permanent Death.%c
ECHO PLAYER The Sentences That May Be Imposed By An Authorized Judge Of
ECHO PLAYER Fayd, In Order Of Severity Include: Fines, Single Death,
ECHO PLAYER Banishment From The City, Obliteration (Permanent Death).
ECHO PLAYER Obliteration Is Reserved Only For Repeating The Most Hideous
ECHO PLAYER Of Crimes.%c
ENDIF

